<p><sup><a href="#_ftnref42" name="_ftn42">42</a> </sup>Adrian Fort, <em>Archibald Wavell: The Life and Death of the Imperial Servant</em> (New York: Vintage Publishing, 2009), 362, 364.</p>
<p><sup><a href="#_ftnref43" name="_ftn43">43</a> </sup>Abhijit Sarkar, “Fed by Famine,” <em>Modern Asian Studies</em> 54 (1), 2020, 2022–86. Dr. Sarkar’s figure of 3.5 million is at the highest end of estimates, which range from 1 million upwards. Precision is impossible given different accounting periods, criteria and agencies.</p>
