<div class="comment-text">
<p>One should rate all of Churchill’s pluses and minuses out of a 1,000. Some of his comments that anybody in the modern era would criticize are perhaps worth 10. Recognizing Hitler’s evil fantasies early and ensuring national and Western survival in 1940 should be rated 990. Simplistic but true. Without him as PM in 1940 many of us would never have been borne, maybe some of the panelists. We owe the Last Lion our immeasurable gratitude</p>
</div>
